SIMPLE: rejuvenescence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rejuvenescence
<hw>Re*ju`ve*nes"cence</hw> <pr>(-n?s"s<it>e</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A renewing of youth; the state of being or growing
young again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A method of cell formation in
which the entire protoplasm of an old cell escapes by rupture of the
cell wall, and then develops a new cell wall. It is seen sometimes in
the formation of zoospores, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejuvenescency</ent>⟦br⟧
